reviewText: Im a Turbo Jam lover, but I have to say that this one (and Fat Blaster) are my least favorite.  At the front of the workout Chalene says that its not as dancey - and she is right.  Its definitely not as much fun as the Cardio Party videos.  Its way too long, seems to drag on forever at 50 minutes.  Also to me some of the footwork at the end is hard to keep up with, especially the Capoiera Cooldown.  By that point Im spent and the last thing I want to do are fancy steps when my patience is up and my body feels like Jello.

reviewText: I gave this video 3 stars just because it is the fast-paced movement that the average person needs to increase cardiovascular fitness. This was the first DVD I had ever done from the Turbo Jam line and I cannot help but think that this was an attempt (attempt being the operative word)to bite off of Billy Blanks' Tae Bo. However, comparing the two, I don't feel that this even comes close mainly because of some of the technique. You learn early on that this is not about the boxing technique but about dancing and bopping around while haphazardly flailing your arms. I did not see any precision in the movements. It is also very very repetitive; almost boringly so. There are three main sections denoted by a change of music and within each section you repeat the same set of movements over and over on each side. Then there's a faster-paced breakdown with a bunch of random movements followed by a slower paced capoeira section.If Tae Bo isn't your thing but you like kickboxing or martial arts-style workouts, I recommend Ilaria Montagnani workouts. However, if you like to dance or want a more relaxed workout, then you'll probably be okay with Turbo Jam.

reviewText: This is one of the longer workout videos put out by the Turbo Jam crew, but it's a great video nonetheless.  I've been doing the Turbo Jam workouts for almost 2 years, and have gotten a lot out of these videos (including a better looking body!).  I just started taking Tae Kwon Do lessons with my husband and daughters.  The instructors couldn't believe I'd never done any type of martial arts.  When I explained I knew some of these moves from workout videos, they couldn't beleive it.  Chalene Johnson is great at motivating you, and makes each workout fun.  (Not annoyingly happy like some other gals!).  I love these workouts and would recommend them to anyone!

reviewText: I am a fan of the Turbo Series and this is ANOTHER great workout from Chalene Johnson (the instructor). There is lots of kicking, punching (jabs, etc) and its very fun. This workout is almost an hour long, and it makes you SWEAT. I find that this workout tightens up every muscle in your body from your arms, abs, butt and thighs. If you are just looking to tone your body this would be the perfect workout for you. Its not too intense, and there is no jumping so your knees are safe. With Punch, Kick, Jam its so fun you wont even realize you are working out, its a dance party! :)

reviewText: This is a wonderful high intensity workout.  If you haven't tried Turbo Jam, you are in for a real workout treat!  Chalene takes what might be boring punch and kick moves and turns them into exciting ab core exercises that really get you motivated and working out!  This is one of my favorite workout DVD's in the Turbo collection.  She has some wonderful combination moves that are great and get you pumped.  I've been doing Turbo Jam for a short while but lost weight and inches (read my review on Turbo Jam Fat Blaster).  This is a great workout DVD.  The moves are designed to flow with your own natural movement and there is a team member on all the DVD's, Mindy, who always does the modified version for those who need a little boost.  For the rest of us, these moves can be pumped higher and hotter to get the best cardio workout.  If you don't know about Chalene and her infectious smile and truly inspirational workout spirit, you are missing out on a great thing! This DVD has about six minutes of warm up which starts off hot and moves into the rest of its 48 minutes (total) of hard workout.  The end of the DVD has some tubular toning, just a couple of minutes or so. The tube thing is a rubber band with handles to work the deltoids and glutes (butt muscles) to tone.  I think it was a way to introduce the tube idea - I'm not so crazy about it.  (Producers should let her do what she does best and thats pump, punch, kick and jam).  On the other hand, the tubes help you learn balance and coordination which calls for a different use of your muscles.) The DVD ends with about a three minute stretching routine.  I do the tube stuff at the end as part of a cool down anyway. My only personal bias is that I wish they would have lengthened the cardio by a few minutes and dumped the tubular stuff.  You will however get your total cardio workout and will feel it at the end.  It's a great routine by design, it is a total workout and one of my absolute best in my collection.  The DVD is about 50 minutes long in total workout time.
summary: One of my absolute favorite Turbo Jam DVD!
